reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great shoe rack
reviews.reviewText: Sturdy,easy to put together, looks good, enough space to sit and wear the shoes too. Love it. Need to see how long it lasts though as i just bought it

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This was exactly what I was looking for for our entryway from the garage. It is sturdy and looks great. Packaging was great and there were no damages. Took about half an hour to assemble by myself with no other tools required. Instructions were easy to follow.Fits my (size 9.5-10 women’s), my husband’s (size 10-10.5 men’s), and toddler’s shoes without issue. The smaller shelf is perfect for her to sit and put her shoes on.I spent HOURS researching shoe storage and finally decided on this. We don’t have a lot of room to work with so we had to find something compact but holds a decent amount. Would definitely recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Absolutely love the look. Fits perfectly in the space I needed it to. It's very stylish and was super easy to assemble. Fit 15 pairs of shoes/boots.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Capacity from pictures is misleading
reviews.reviewText: The shoe rack is very nice, I love the way it looks and fully assembled it seems to be sturdy so far. The measurements they give are accurate, but the photo shopped pictures of their product showing shoes on it is misleading to say the least.The 4 smaller shelves can fit 3 pairs of shoes if the aren't too chunky, but hight wise a small ankle boot will be a tight fit. The taller shelf can fit two pairs of shoes and maybe one more solo shoe.So ya overall I like the shoe rack and since a looked at the measurements and compared them to my needs it was a good purchase for me. Though if you have more decorative chunky shoes this rack might not be what you need, or if you have a lot of taller shoes or boots.Hope this helps!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly what I was looking for!
reviews.reviewText: This bench was exactly what I was looking for for our small laundry room/ garage entryway! It was easy to put together and seems to be good quality! The rack that the shoes go on is a hard metal mesh. The top bench part looks nice and works great for a bench or area to hold purses/ backpacks. Bonus was I had baskets that fit in one of the shelves to keep gloves/ hats in! Overall, I am very happy and would definitely recommend this bench!

reviews.reviewText: I looked for a few weeks trying to figure out what type of shoe rack I wanted and I’m so glad I went with this one! reviews.reviewTitle: Versatile and Easy Assembly – Ideal for Shoe Storage, Caution Advised for Seating
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this 3-tier shoe rack bench for my entryway and have found it to be a practical addition to my home. Assembly was a breeze, which is always a plus. Its main strength lies in its storage capability – it efficiently organizes shoes and boots, keeping my entryway tidy. The top tier provides a convenient surface for setting down items like keys and mail when coming and going.Although it is marketed as a bench, I would exercise caution when using it for seating. While it's sturdy enough to hold various footwear and miscellaneous items, it doesn't inspire confidence as a seat. It seems to be more reliable for lighter loads, and I'm hesitant to put my full weight on it regularly.For anyone looking to streamline their shoe storage without sacrificing style, this shoe rack bench is a solid choice. Just be mindful that it might be best reserved for lighter use if you're considering it for a seat.
